post_text: Our Middle School Students have been doing a great job wearing their masks all day at school! But if you know Middle Schoolers, you won’t be surprised that we have had some mask malfunctions - broken earloops, students who forgot to bring them in the morning and who knows what tomorrow will bring! We are also encouraging students to wear a new disposable mask each day or have a spare fabric mask, so they can be washed. We are looking for donations of fabric or disposable masks for students that could use a spare! All Care Closet donations or hygiene items or masks can be dropped off at the Middle School during school hours.

post_text:
We are happy to say that we were able to help over 30 families at the Care Closet last week! So we need to replenish our supplies! We have added to our Amazon list if you are interested in donating. You are not required to purchase the items from Amazon, we are just trying to make it easier if that is what you prefer. In addition to the items on the list, we are looking for towels and washcloths and blankets.

We think students will need iPad styluses and earbuds to help them work on their devices this year, both in school and at home.

We are still not ready to take clothing items - we know you are anxiously waiting! We are going to clear out the bags of donations we have not sorted through and then we will be ready to take donations again!

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/31IBKNZP0LHEV?ref_=wl_share

post_text:
So many have asked how to help us give kids what they need - so here are a few ways!
1. Cash or gift cards such as Walmart, Dollar General, Amazon and Weis. This allows us to buy specific items that students need.
2. Purchase hygiene items such as shampoo, conditioner, soap, toothpaste, and deodorant.

At this time, we are not accepting clothing donations.

Donations can be dropped off at the Middle School Tuesdays and Wednesdays 8-12 or mailed to the district office: JSASD 175 A & P Drive, Jersey Shore PA 17740.

In addition to in-store purchases, you can use our Amazon wish list in the link below. Any brands and quantities of the items listed are needed, as we are currently running low on hygiene items. Amazon purchases can be shipped directly to the administration office at the address above.

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/31IBKNZP0LHEV?ref_=wl_share

We appreciate your continued support of the JSMS Care Closet!!

post_text:
The JSMS Care Closet team appreciates all the donations of clothing we have been receiving! We have been able to help so many of our students! One of our goals when we started was to share with the students in other schools in the district. We are creating boxes of hygiene items to be kept in the nurse’s offices so they are available to students in need all over Jersey Shore Area School District. We are able to meet this need because of the generosity of the Jersey Shore community!

At this time, here is a list of our biggest needs. As always, we will continue to collect clothing and other hygiene items!
1. Hats, scarves and gloves.
2. Sneakers - all sizes - new and gently used. Greatest need are male styles.
3. Shampoo and conditioner
4. Laundry detergent - free of dyes and perfumes is preferred.
5. Odd request - Shoe Size Device - anyone have one laying around? This would be nice to make things go quicker!

If you have some that you don’t need, we could definitely use them!

post_text: Just over 50% of the population of Jersey Shore Area Middle School is considered economically disadvantaged. This can mean that things like clothes and hygiene items are difficult to purchase or that it is difficult to have clean clothes. The goal of the JSMS Care Closet is to help students worry less about these things and be able to focus on their school work. We will provide basic hygiene items, everyday clothing and clothing for special occasions like school dances and concerts. Donations can be made at the JSMS Main Office during regular school hours.
